,Recommended,394160,32752022,Posted: 24 June,all,Justiguy,"What can be said about Pac-Man that hasn't been said dozens of times already? The game isn't a classic for no reason. The gameplay is addictive and iconic, and as soon as you hear those jingles, beeps, boops, and waka wakas, you'll very likely find them stuck in your head for the rest of the day, if not longer.So how's this PORT of Pac-Man, then?Well, as far as the game itself is concerned, it's Pac-Man! Looks nice, plays great, sounds like the Pac-Man you'd expect.That said, the ""ARCADE GAME SERIES"" version of Pac-Man here does have a couple of kinks in it, the main one I found being that you do have to play it while most of the screen is taken up with artwork like an old school arcade cabinet, but the game itself is as playable and addictive as it's always been.Despite that, if you want some old school arcade fun to pick up and play without having to worry about the modern video game stresses of story modes, load times, and so on, then this is definitely worth the purchase."
