76561197982175416,Recommended,394160,26057492,"Posted: 15 October, 2016",all,Retro,"About as close to owning an actual Pac-Man arcade machine as you'll get.  Remember the days of yore when you'd drop a $5 bill in the change machine at the arcade and have a blast?  Grab one of those fivers and get Pac-Man.Authentic arcade emulation.Adjustable zoom level or custom scaling / rotation to accomodate a variety of possible monitors you might rig up, such as a flat panel that you can rotate, or an old-school CRT monitor.Adjustable custom scanlines function:  adds a filter that you can increase or decrease to create that authentic pixellated CRT aperture grille and scaling effectBezel art can be switched between two different options or toggled off.Numerous adjustable audio options to create that authentic 'arcade feel' on your sound system.Comments:Some people have written negative reviews without bothering to play with the settings.Fullscreen mode: it the game supports windowed-borderless.  To get to this just keep toggling the window size settings until you get there.Quitting your session:  hit start or the <ESC> key and then select ""return to main menu.""  No, you don't need to hit ALT-F4 to quit your pac-man session and try again. :P"
